      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "It seems to me this adds more function calls to more complicated functions to give os-specific path separators when, though an os may prefer one or another, it accepts both.  So it seems like this just slows down and complicates non-performance-critical code for absolutely no reason?\n",
